Singapore Petroleum Co Pte Ltd willrevise pump prices of petrol from June 2, an official said.    Grade 97 octane with 0.15 gm/lead will be 96.8 cents/litreagainst 94 cents previously for 0.4 gm lead. Grade 92 octanewill be 90.6 cents against 87.6 previously.    SPC's price revision follows the Ministry of Trade andIndustry's move to liberalise petrol pricing by allowing oilcompanies to set their own pump prices.    New grades of petrol with lower lead content are sold inSingapore from today in line with the Ministry of Environment'sregulations. REUTER&#3;